{
  "page": "Two Kings",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Two_Kings.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/de/Two_Kings.png/300px-Two_Kings.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"173\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/de/Two_Kings.png/450px-Two_Kings.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/de/Two_Kings.png/600px-Two_Kings.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Two_Kings.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Mern IX Gardener and Loren I Lannister, as depicted in <i>Conquest &amp; Rebellion: An Animated History of the Seven Kingdoms</i></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Two Kings</b> is the nickname used to refer to <a href=\"/index.php/Mern_IX_Gardener\" title=\"Mern IX Gardener\">Mern IX Gardener</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Loren_I_Lannister\" title=\"Loren I Lannister\">Loren I Lannister</a>, the last <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Reach\" title=\"King of the Reach\">King of the Reach</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Rock\" title=\"King of the Rock\">King of the Rock</a>, respectively.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Two_Kings&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Loren_I_Lannister\" title=\"Loren I Lannister\">Loren I Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Mern_IX_Gardener\" title=\"Mern IX Gardener\">Mern IX Gardener</a> formed an alliance between the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> in order to resist <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a>, the recently-proclaimed <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_All_Westeros\" title=\"King of All Westeros\">King of All Westeros</a>. Together, they commanded an army of fifty-five thousand men, the mightiest host ever assembled in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> thus far. Their impressive numbers were no match for the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>, however. Mern died in the <a href=\"/index.php/Field_of_Fire\" title=\"Field of Fire\">Field of Fire</a> along with all his kin from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Gardener\" title=\"House Gardener\">House Gardener</a>. Loren survived the battle but bent the knee to Aegon the Conqueror the following day.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Two_Kings&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Aegon's Conquest.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404210510\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.013 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.015 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 214/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8572/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 534/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 178/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 899/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    7.346      1 -total\n 78.72%    5.783      2 Template:Ref\n 48.50%    3.563      2 Template:Ref/core\n 19.51%    1.433      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:27355-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404210510 and revision id 309133\n -->\n",
